On Tue, 19 Feb 2002, Sean Bartnik wrote:

> Hi all,
> OK, after many helpful list responses and calling around to my local shop
> and the tire companies, it looks like my main choices are thus:
> 
> Michelin Agilis61 in 185R14 at about $120/tire.
> 
> Continental CR21 reinforced (load range C) in 185R14 at about $80/tire.
> 
> Yokohama Y356 in 185R14, price unknown (anybody want to let me know?)
> 
> Kumho Commercial A/S 852 in 185R14C load range D, price unknown.
> 
> I'm going to be getting 2 tires.  Since the MX that I have on my van is out
> of production and I don't want to mix tread patterns, I'm going to replace
> my slashed tire with a new one and then put another new one on the other
> side, making the leftover MX my spare tire since my spare tire is a
> different size and barely holds air (wouldn't drive on it except in an
> emergency!)
> As it is I'm very strongly leaning toward the Michelin but the price on that
> Continental is looking pretty decent.  Is the Michelin really $40 better?
> 
> I know Michelin makes great tires but I've never had Continental tires
> before on anything.
> 
> The Yokohama has also gotten pretty good reviews on the list.  I seem to
> recall from back in the day that the Y356 was a highway-rib tire but those
> listmembers who have them tell me they are great in snow and rain.  Anyone
> have an approximate price?
> 
> I got one suggestion for the Kumho though I must admit I am a little leery
> of these South Korean tires, even though I have heard some good things.  Kia
> and Daewoo have for me put a bad spin on all South Korean products :-)
> Anyone have a price for these?
> 
> I'm pretty much going to go with either the Michelin or the Continental
> unless someone can make a really really strong case for the Yoko or the
> Kumho.  I'd love to hear of anyone's experience with the Continental
> especially, since no one mentioned them to me aside from Karl.  I had
> Yokohama tires on a Mercedes I once had and they seemed pretty good but they
> were passenger car tires, and that's another world :-)
> 
> Thanks for all your help, folks.  Vandals suck!
> 
> Sean Bartnik
